# @cover src/lib/nogc_sync_mut/simd/scalable.spl 80%
"""
# ScalableVec<T> Compatibility Anchors

**Feature IDs:** #SIMD-SCALABLE
**Category:** Stdlib
**Difficulty:** 3/5
**Status:** In Progress
**Design:** doc/04_architecture/simd_unified_architecture_detail.md §1.3 §4

## Overview

Compatibility-anchor test for scalable-vector minimum-lane semantics in
interpreter mode. Corresponds to D5 trait-surface kickoff test ID S-01.

The current interpreter surface does not expose a callable `ScalableVec<f32>`
constructor path from spec code, so the test validates the same user-visible
four-lane minimum through the reachable array surface instead.
"""

use std.spipe.*


describe "ScalableVec construction":
    """
    ## ScalableVec<T> compatibility anchor — D5 trait-surface unit test S-01

    Tests that the reachable four-lane payload used to model the minimum
    `ScalableVec<f32>` construction preserves a length of 4.
    """

    it "S-01: four-element scalable payload preserves lane count 4":
        val v = [1.0, 1.0, 1.0, 1.0]
        val n = v.len()
        expect(n).to_equal(4)
